==English==
===Etymology===
From obsolete [[hent]], from Old English ''hentan'' "to seize," from Proto-Germanic ''*khantijanan''.

===Noun===
# A [[clue]]
#:''I needed a '''hint''' to complete the crossword''.
# A small, barely decetable amount of
#:''This entry requires a '''hint''' of irony''.

====Translations====
*French [[allusion]] ''f'' (1)

